{
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/main/sarif-2.1/schema/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "fullName": "Trivy Vulnerability Scanner",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy",
          "name": "Trivy",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "DS-0001",
              "name": "Misconfiguration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "':latest' tag used"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When using a 'FROM' statement you should use a specific tag to avoid uncontrolled behavior when the image is updated."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0001",
              "help": {
                "text": "Misconfiguration DS-0001\nType: Dockerfile Security Check\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nCheck: ':latest' tag used\nMessage: Specify a tag in the 'FROM' statement for image 'ubuntu'\nLink: [DS-0001](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0001)\nWhen using a 'FROM' statement you should use a specific tag to avoid uncontrolled behavior when the image is updated.",
                "markdown": "**Misconfiguration DS-0001**\n| Type | Severity | Check | Message | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|Dockerfile Security Check|MEDIUM|':latest' tag used|Specify a tag in the 'FROM' statement for image 'ubuntu'|[DS-0001](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0001)|\n\nWhen using a 'FROM' statement you should use a specific tag to avoid uncontrolled behavior when the image is updated."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
                  "misconfiguration",
                  "security",
                  "MEDIUM"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "DS-0002",
              "name": "Misconfiguration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Image user should not be 'root'"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Running containers with 'root' user can lead to a container escape situation. It is a best practice to run containers as non-root users, which can be done by adding a 'USER' statement to the Dockerfile."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0002",
              "help": {
                "text": "Misconfiguration DS-0002\nType: Dockerfile Security Check\nSeverity: HIGH\nCheck: Image user should not be 'root'\nMessage: Last USER command in Dockerfile should not be 'root'\nLink: [DS-0002](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0002)\nRunning containers with 'root' user can lead to a container escape situation. It is a best practice to run containers as non-root users, which can be done by adding a 'USER' statement to the Dockerfile.",
                "markdown": "**Misconfiguration DS-0002**\n| Type | Severity | Check | Message | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|Dockerfile Security Check|HIGH|Image user should not be 'root'|Last USER command in Dockerfile should not be 'root'|[DS-0002](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0002)|\n\nRunning containers with 'root' user can lead to a container escape situation. It is a best practice to run containers as non-root users, which can be done by adding a 'USER' statement to the Dockerfile."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "8.0",
                "tags": [
                  "misconfiguration",
                  "security",
                  "HIGH"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "DS-0004",
              "name": "Misconfiguration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Port 22 exposed"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Exposing port 22 might allow users to SSH into the container."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0004",
              "help": {
                "text": "Misconfiguration DS-0004\nType: Dockerfile Security Check\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nCheck: Port 22 exposed\nMessage: Port 22 should not be exposed in Dockerfile\nLink: [DS-0004](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0004)\nExposing port 22 might allow users to SSH into the container.",
                "markdown": "**Misconfiguration DS-0004**\n| Type | Severity | Check | Message | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|Dockerfile Security Check|MEDIUM|Port 22 exposed|Port 22 should not be exposed in Dockerfile|[DS-0004](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0004)|\n\nExposing port 22 might allow users to SSH into the container."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
                  "misconfiguration",
                  "security",
                  "MEDIUM"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "DS-0026",
              "name": "Misconfiguration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "No HEALTHCHECK defined"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "You should add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your docker container images to perform the health check on running containers."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0026",
              "help": {
                "text": "Misconfiguration DS-0026\nType: Dockerfile Security Check\nSeverity: LOW\nCheck: No HEALTHCHECK defined\nMessage: Add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your Dockerfile\nLink: [DS-0026](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0026)\nYou should add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your docker container images to perform the health check on running containers.",
                "markdown": "**Misconfiguration DS-0026**\n| Type | Severity | Check | Message | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|Dockerfile Security Check|LOW|No HEALTHCHECK defined|Add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your Dockerfile|[DS-0026](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0026)|\n\nYou should add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your docker container images to perform the health check on running containers."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "2.0",
                "tags": [
                  "misconfiguration",
                  "security",
                  "LOW"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "DS-0029",
              "name": "Misconfiguration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "'apt-get' missing '--no-install-recommends'"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "'apt-get' install should use '--no-install-recommends' to minimize image size."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0029",
              "help": {
                "text": "Misconfiguration DS-0029\nType: Dockerfile Security Check\nSeverity: HIGH\nCheck: 'apt-get' missing '--no-install-recommends'\nMessage: '--no-install-recommends' flag is missed: 'apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl'\nLink: [DS-0029](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0029)\n'apt-get' install should use '--no-install-recommends' to minimize image size.",
                "markdown": "**Misconfiguration DS-0029**\n| Type | Severity | Check | Message | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|Dockerfile Security Check|HIGH|'apt-get' missing '--no-install-recommends'|'--no-install-recommends' flag is missed: 'apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl'|[DS-0029](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0029)|\n\n'apt-get' install should use '--no-install-recommends' to minimize image size."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "8.0",
                "tags": [
                  "misconfiguration",
                  "security",
                  "HIGH"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "DS-0001",
          "ruleIndex": 0,
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Artifact: Dockerfile\nType: dockerfile\nVulnerability DS-0001\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nMessage: Specify a tag in the 'FROM' statement for image 'ubuntu'\nLink: [DS-0001](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0001)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "Dockerfile",
                  "uriBaseId": "ROOTPATH"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 1,
                  "startColumn": 1,
                  "endLine": 1,
                  "endColumn": 1
                }
              },
              "message": {
                "text": "Dockerfile"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "DS-0002",
          "ruleIndex": 1,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Artifact: Dockerfile\nType: dockerfile\nVulnerability DS-0002\nSeverity: HIGH\nMessage: Last USER command in Dockerfile should not be 'root'\nLink: [DS-0002](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0002)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "Dockerfile",
                  "uriBaseId": "ROOTPATH"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 2,
                  "startColumn": 1,
                  "endLine": 2,
                  "endColumn": 1
                }
              },
              "message": {
                "text": "Dockerfile"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "DS-0004",
          "ruleIndex": 2,
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Artifact: Dockerfile\nType: dockerfile\nVulnerability DS-0004\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nMessage: Port 22 should not be exposed in Dockerfile\nLink: [DS-0004](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0004)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "Dockerfile",
                  "uriBaseId": "ROOTPATH"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 4,
                  "startColumn": 1,
                  "endLine": 4,
                  "endColumn": 1
                }
              },
              "message": {
                "text": "Dockerfile"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "DS-0026",
          "ruleIndex": 3,
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "Artifact: Dockerfile\nType: dockerfile\nVulnerability DS-0026\nSeverity: LOW\nMessage: Add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your Dockerfile\nLink: [DS-0026](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0026)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "Dockerfile",
                  "uriBaseId": "ROOTPATH"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 1,
                  "startColumn": 1,
                  "endLine": 1,
                  "endColumn": 1
                }
              },
              "message": {
                "text": "Dockerfile"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "DS-0029",
          "ruleIndex": 4,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Artifact: Dockerfile\nType: dockerfile\nVulnerability DS-0029\nSeverity: HIGH\nMessage: '--no-install-recommends' flag is missed: 'apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl'\nLink: [DS-0029](https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/ds-0029)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "Dockerfile",
                  "uriBaseId": "ROOTPATH"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 3,
                  "startColumn": 1,
                  "endLine": 3,
                  "endColumn": 1
                }
              },
              "message": {
                "text": "Dockerfile"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "columnKind": "utf16CodeUnits"
    }
  ]
}
